<subSubSection id="7EA86509FFF4031CFC1B294A55E067C7" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="221" pageId="0" pageNumber="220" type="description">
<paragraph id="360D3682FFF4031CFC1B294A576966AC" blockId="0.[804,1475,1842,1890]" lastBlockId="1.[114,785,1151,1477]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="221" pageId="0" pageNumber="220">is intensely attacked by the galler. Galls are arranged in groups or separately, on the abaxial surface of apical leaves, near the leaf veins. Asingle galling larva is found in each gall, where the pupation occurs. Adults emerge by an opening situated adaxially.</paragraph>
